The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 04 January is 154,348 (17,789.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 December, there were 11,542 new confirmed cases (1,330.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 December, there were 9,163 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 26% (2,379 extra cases).
